# Google OAuth Configuration for Obsidian GCal Sync
# ---------------------------------------------
# Follow these steps to set up your environment:
#
# 1. Create a project in Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/)
# 2. Enable the Google Calendar API for your project
# 3. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Web application type)
# 4. Set authorized redirect URIs:
#    - For desktop: http://localhost:8085
#    - For mobile: https://obsidian-gcal-sync.netlify.app/.netlify/functions/auth
# 5. Copy your Client ID below
# 6. Rename this file to .env (remove the .template extension)
#
# IMPORTANT: Never share your .env file or commit it to version control!

# Your Google OAuth Client ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_CLIENT_ID_HERE

# Note: Client Secret is only used by the Netlify authentication service
# and is stored securely in the Netlify environment. You do not need
# to configure it here. 